4","1537":"1537","of England":"England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Starlyng","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Norfolk): variant of   Sterling   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Stallings","meanings":["English: prrobably an altered form of   Starling  . This surname is also common among African Americans.","Americanized form of German   Stalling  .","History: The majority of the American bearers of this surname trace their origin to Nicholas Stallings from England, who settled in VA in the 17th century."]},{"name":"Sterling","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Stirling  .","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Starling</i>, <i>Sterling</i> (Old English <i>Stærling</i>), itself from the bird-name, whose use as a nickname may also be another source of the surname. Compare   Stare   2.","German: from Middle High German <i>sterlinc</i>, the name of a coin, hence probably a nickname for someone who paid that amount in rent."]},{"name":"Starlin","meanings":["English: altered form of   Starling  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Starlyng was born about 1500, in Essex, England, United Kingdom as the son of Robert Starlyng. He married Mrs. Rose Starling about 1514, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died before October 1537, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1500–Bef October 1537":"umbes 1500–enne oktoobrit 1537","1500–1537":"1500–1537","1499–1562":"1499–1562","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1460–1504":"1460–1504","Bef October 1537":"enne oktoobrit 1537","Abt 1500":"umbes 1500","1460":"1460","Abt 1514":"umbes 1514","1500":"1500","Bef 23 September 1504":"enne 23. septembrit 1504","Abt 1520":"umbes 1520","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1584":"1584","1562":"1562","1504":"1504","1537":"1537","of England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1500–Bef October 1537":"noin 1500–ennen vuotta lokakuu 1537","1500–1537":"1500–1537","1499–1562":"1499–1562","1520–1584":"1520–1584","1460–1504":"1460–1504","Bef October 1537":"ennen vuotta lokakuu 1537","Abt 1500":"noin 1500","1460":"1460","Abt 1514":"noin 1514","1500":"1500","Bef 23 September 1504":"ennen vuotta 23. syyskuuta 1504","Abt 1520":"noin 1520","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1584":"1584","1562":"1562","1504":"1504","1537":"1537","of England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunt